---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import { getSeason } from '../lib/season';

const season = getSeason();
const seasonLabel = season.charAt(0).toUpperCase() + season.slice(1);
---

<Base title="Now — Christopher Rangel" description="What Christopher Rangel is designing, baking, photographing, and learning right now">
	<div class="container">
		<section class="hero">
			<h1>Now</h1>
			<p class="page-meta">Last updated: June 2026 &middot; {seasonLabel}</p>
		</section>
		<div class="prose">
			<h3>Designing</h3>
			<p>
				Like a lot of companies right now, work has meant figuring out how to put AI to good
				use inside the enterprise, including how it can interact with mock data for features
				we're still exploring. Outside of work, that same curiosity is pointed at myself:
				poking at AI and new tools, and taking it far enough to host this portfolio myself
				instead of leaving it on Squarespace.
			</p>
			<h3>Baking</h3>
			<p>
				Not much baking lately, if I'm honest. The hobby of the moment is keeping my plants
				alive and picking up new tech skills along the way.
			</p>
			<h3>Photographing</h3>
			<p>
				Spring, easily. I grew up in California, so the bloom here in Richmond is a
				completely different cast of characters than what I'm used to. I miss birds of
				paradise, but the sheer number of hydrangeas more than makes up for it. There's also
				one gorgeous purple flower around the neighborhood I still haven't identified.
			</p>
			<h3>Learning in Astro</h3>
			<p>
				Moving off Squarespace, I underestimated how much flexibility I'd get back. Astro
				lets in all the small, specific design details that make this site feel like mine.
				It's the kind of thing Squarespace wasn't built to allow.
			</p>
		</div>
	</div>
</Base>
